p
cd\leq\frac{c^p}{p}+\frac{d^q}{q}
\frac{1}{p}+\frac{1}{q}=1
c=\frac{|f(t)|}{\left(\int_{a}^{b}|f(t)|^p dt\right)^\frac{1}{p}}
d=\frac{|g(t)|}{\left(\int_{a}^{b}|g(t)|^q dt\right)^\frac{1}{q}},
\int_{a}^{b}|f(t)g(t)|dt\leq\left(\int_{a}^{b}|f(t)|^p dt\right)^\frac{1}{p}\left(\int_{a}^{b}|g(t)|^q dt\right)^\frac{1}{q}.
f,g \in L_{p}[a,b]
\int_{a}^{b}|f+g|^{p}=\int_{a}^{b}|f+g|^{p-1}|f+g|
\le\int_{a}^{b}|f+g|^{p-1}(|f|+|g|) \text{ by triangle inequality of absolute value function}
=\int_{a}^{b}|f+g|^{p-1}|f|+\int_{a}^{b}|f+g|^{p-1}|g|
